===全球暖化===
{{see also|全球暖化}}
北極熊面臨的危機中，影響最大、最立即的是全球暖化,
<ref>{{Cite web |URL=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/09/150904-polar-bears-dolphins-seals-climate-change |title=4 Ways Polar Bears Are Dealing With Climate Change. |accessdate=2016-08-30 |archive-date=2016-08-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828161254/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/09/150904-polar-bears-dolphins-seals-climate-change/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
<ref>{{Cite web |URL= https://www.skepticalscience.com/polar-bears-global-warming.htm |title= How will global warming affect polar bears? |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2016-09-09 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160909164233/http://www.skepticalscience.com/polar-bears-global-warming.htm |dead-url= no }}</ref>
。由于全球暖化發生速度極快，讓依赖北極[[海冰|海冰]]生存的北極熊，無法因應。北極熊需要海冰來捕食海豹、賴以生存，全球暖化嚴重地導致北極冰層大量地、快速地消失<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://nsidc.org/arcticseaicenews/charctic-interactive-sea-ice-graph |title= Interactive Sea Ice Graph |accessdate= 2016-08-28 |archive-date= 2016-08-28 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160828030018/http://nsidc.org/arcticseaicenews/charctic-interactive-sea-ice-graph/ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://www.geoengineeringwatch.org/the-ice-melts-into-water |title= the ice melt into water |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2017-01-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170111084321/http://www.geoengineeringwatch.org/the-ice-melts-into-water/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>在過去25年來，夏季的海冰已多融化了超過50萬平方英里，相當於130萬平方公尺，近台灣的40倍大面積、比整個內蒙古自治區還大
<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://alaska.usgs.gov/science/biology/polar_bears/pbear_sea_ice.html |title= Polar Bear-Sea Ice Relationships |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2016-06-16 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160616201719/http://alaska.usgs.gov/science/biology/polar_bears/pbear_sea_ice.html |dead-url= no }}  Over the past 25 years, the summer sea ice melt period has lengthened, and summer sea ice cover has declined by over half a million square miles.</ref>，全面性威脅到整個北極圈生物生存<ref>{{Cite book | author = Andrew E. Decocher | title = Polar Bears : A complete guide to their biology and behaviour | publisher = The John Hopskins University Press | date = 2012 |  pages = 199 | ISBN = 978-1-4214-0305-2 | language = en }} page 218 Global warming is the greatest threat facing polar bears not mearly threaten individual bears, It threatens the entire species</ref><ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://www.greenfacts.org/en/arctic-climate-change/index.htm#2 |title= Arctic Climate Change : 5. How will animals be affected by Arctic warming? |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2007-02-07 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070207083204/http://www.greenfacts.org/en/arctic-climate-change/index.htm#2 |dead-url= no }}</ref>。不止是北極熊需要海冰來生存，海豹也需要靠海冰來哺育他們的下一代<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://ocean.si.edu/blog/ice-loving-seals-and-loss-sea-ice |title= Ice-Loving Seals and the Loss of Sea Ice |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2016-09-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160913133930/http://ocean.si.edu/blog/ice-loving-seals-and-loss-sea-ice |dead-url= no }}</ref>。當海冰消失時，其他原本被海冰阻絕於外的海洋動物，如殺人鯨等、也會有機會進入原本牠們無法進入的北極區，進而又影響當地生態<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://www.worldwildlife.org/stories/as-arctic-ice-melts-orcas-move-in |title= As Arctic Ice Melts, Orcas Move in |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2016-11-18 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20161118094201/http://www.worldwildlife.org/stories/as-arctic-ice-melts-orcas-move-in |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

北極熊因全球暖化所造成的海冰減少、以致捕獵的機會降低、食物來源不足，科學家觀察追踪到的現象有：成熊平均體重的下降、小北極熊和年輕北極熊存活率嚴重降低、懷孕母熊的儲脂量減少、小熊平均孕育隻數減低等 <ref>{{Cite book | author = Andrew E. Decocher | title = Polar Bears : A complete guide to their biology and behaviour | publisher = The John Hopskins University Press | date = 2012 |  pages = 217 | ISBN = 978-1-4214-0305-2 | language = en }} chapter : Threat, page 217</ref>。一般新聞可見的現象則有：北極熊冒險爬上懸岸覓食<ref name="auto2"/><ref name="auto3"/><ref name="auto4"/>、冒淹死的危險長游覓食<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2011/07/110720-polar-bears-global-warming-sea-ice-science-environment |title= Longest Polar Bear Swim Recorded—426 Miles Straight |accessdate= 2016-08-29 |archive-date= 2016-09-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160911023445/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2011/07/110720-polar-bears-global-warming-sea-ice-science-environment/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>、闖進人類社區覓食、公熊追殺吃食小熊<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://www.livescience.com/17500-global-warming-driving-polar-bears-cannibalism.html |title= Is Global Warming Driving Polar Bears to Cannibalism? |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2016-09-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160911143057/http://www.livescience.com/17500-global-warming-driving-polar-bears-cannibalism.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>等等。

科學家認為，如果全球暖化的速率不減，可能在本世紀中，北極熊的數量會銳減2/3，本世紀末是否會全面滅絕，則是未可知<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://blog.nature.org/science/2013/12/03/what-science-polar-bear/ |title= Will Polar Bears Die Out Because of Climate Change? |accessdate= 2016-08-30 |archive-date= 2016-09-15 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160915003922/http://blog.nature.org/science/2013/12/03/what-science-polar-bear/ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://kids.nationalgeographic.com/kids/stories/animalsnature/polar-bears-threatened/ |title= Polar Bears Listed as Threatened |accessdate= 2016-08-29 |archive-date= 2016-09-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160911032342/http://kids.nationalgeographic.com/kids/stories/animalsnature/polar-bears-threatened/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

===人為污染===

如同[[全球暖化|全球暖化]]，人為所造成的污染，也整個影響及北極圈所有生物的健康與生態<ref>{{Cite web |URL= http://pollutionarticles.blogspot.com/2011/05/how-is-pollution-affecting-polar-bears.html |title= How is pollution affecting polar bears? |accessdate= 2016-08-29 |archive-date= 2016-10-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20161013162130/http://pollutionarticles.blogspot.com/2011/05/how-is-pollution-affecting-polar-bears.html |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |URL= 
